  "text": "The LLVM loop vectorization infrastructure is composed of several key components:\n\n1. **LoopVectorizePass (Main Pass Implementation)**:\n   - Header: llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.h (lines 130-166)\n   - Implementation: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp\n   - This is the main pass that drives the vectorization process in LLVM. It coordinates the other components.\n\n2. **LoopVectorizeOptions (Pass Configuration)**:\n   - File: llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.h (lines 85-119)\n   - This struct defines configuration options for the LoopVectorizePass, including InterleaveOnlyWhenForced and VectorizeOnlyWhenForced flags.\n\n3. **LoopVectorizationLegality (Legality Checking)**:\n   - Header: llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorizationLegality.h\n   - Implementation: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorizationLegality.cpp\n   - This class is responsible for checking whether a loop is legal to vectorize, examining data dependencies, memory access patterns, and other constraints.\n\n4. **LoopVectorizationCostModel (Profitability Analysis)**:\n   - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp (class definition starts at line 882)\n   - This class analyzes the cost-benefit of vectorization and decides on optimal vectorization factors. It uses the TargetTransformInfo to estimate instruction costs.\n\n5. **VPlan (Vectorization Plan)**:\n   - Header: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.h (class definition starts at line 4491)\n   - Implementation: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.cpp\n   - VPlan is the primary data structure representing the vectorized loop body in an intermediate representation. It's used in LLVM's modern VPlan-native vectorization path and represents the vectorized computation as a hierarchy of VPBasicBlocks containing recipes.\n\nAll files are located in the github.com/sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d repository, which is a mirror of the LLVM project."
}

